snippet.textDisplay:
If Ruiz stood in the centre of the ring wanting to box there would have been continual boos for 12 rounds because AJ would have pranced about the ropes and not went near Ruiz. To his credit, Ruiz kept going forward towards AJ to fight but could not get close enough, as AJ picked him off with jabs and hooks on the retreat. In a weird and embarrassing interview after the fight AJ pitifully described the art of pugilism, really! - as if we didn’t already know! However, as you might be able to tell, I was not impressed! From this display, I can honestly say that AJ will lose easily, EASILY, against the gypsy king or Wilder.

His ‘team’ will need to protect him from these guys and do some pretty dancing to skirt the possibility of this ever happening!
